		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Republic of Austria is a country located in the South Central part of Europe east of the Alps. Austria was originally occupied by the Celtic tribes until the Romans conquered the land. After the dissolution of the Roman Empire, Austria was invaded in 788 A.D by Charlemagne, the emperor of the Holy Roman Empire. Several hundred years later in, the 12th century, the Habsburg Monarchy began its long dynasty over Austria, lasting 750 years. The Habsburg Monarch developed Austria and made it a center of power in Europe for many centuries. After the first World War in 1919, the empire collapsed and the Austrian Republic was created. In 1938, Austria was annexed by the Austrian -- (native)-- born Adolf Hitler. Many Austrian Jews were killed or forced to emmigrate during the holocaust until 1945. Austria was divided up after the war and did not become an independent country until 1955.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.eurozine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/habsburg_krakow_468w-e1496753986671.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>The Habsburg Monarchy held dynasty over Austria for 750 years</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Today, the Republic of Austria has a parliamentary constitution with a President as the head of state, and a Chancellor as the head of government. Austria is comprised of nine states. One of which, Vienna (the capital), is a city-state. Austria is in the top 20 richest countries in the world, and consistently achieves a high standard of living.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://emerging-europe.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/bigstock-vienna-austria-cityscape-ima-264724732-990x556.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>The Imperial Palace in Vienna, Austria</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The climate of Austria is typically continental, which includes cloudy, cold and rainy, or snowy winters with mild summers. Almost 70% of Austria is covered by the Alps, and only about a quarter of the land is below 1,600 feet of elevation.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				
The nationwide spoken language in Austria is German. However, different states have different ethnic majorities, so other languages are spoken as well. In Carinthia, the official language is Slovene, while in Burgenland the official language is Croatian and Hungarian.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Austria was a culturally and musically influential country for many centuries in Europe. Because of this, Austria was the birthplace for many proficient musical composers such as Joseph Haydn, Johan Strauss and Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart. Austria is also the birthplace of many famous 20th century philosophers including Ludwig Wittgenstein, and Karl Popper.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://d3fr1q02b1tb0i.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/23090606/1-1-scaled.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Vienna State Opera House</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The most popular sport in Austria is Alpine Skiing, which is very important to the promotion and economic growth of the country. Other winter sports popular in Austria are snowboarding and ski jumping.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
